<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{5}{y}={7}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{8}{y}=-{104}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{7}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -8. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{8}}{{-{{7}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{8}}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left(-{7}{x}+{5}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{8}}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left({7}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({8}\right)}{x}+{5.7142857142857}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{8}{y}=-{104}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{13.714285714286}{y}=-{96}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{96}}{{13.714285714286}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{5}{\left(-{7}\right)}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{\left(-{35}\right)}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}={7}-{\left(-{35}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{42}}{{-{{7}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{7}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>